American steel,

23:14.893 --> 23:16.729 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
American labor.

23:16.762 --> 23:21.734 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, using some of Trump's
America-first energy
and broader policy, that's kind
of injected

23:21.767 --> 23:24.370 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
into his approach to pipelines
and infrastructure.

23:24.403 --> 23:28.507 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: More broadly,
I know you
have studied the Obama
administration's environmental

23:28.540 --> 23:32.177 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
policy and then the emerging
Trump administration's
policy.

23:32.211 --> 23:37.549 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
How do these pipeline projects
fit into that
larger vision, as you see it?

23:37.583 --> 23:42.488 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
VALERIE VOLCOVICI: Well,
candidate Trump made
it very clear what he wants to
see.

23:42.521 --> 23:48.961 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He has seen President Obama --
former President
Obama's environmental
regulations as something

23:48.994 --> 23:54.667 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that's choking the U.S. economy,
that's preventing
jobs from being created.

23:54.700 --> 23:58.437 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Former President Obama didn't
really see that
they were an impediment to job
creation.

23:58.470 --> 24:05.611 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he liked to highlight that
U.S. emissions
went down as the economy grew.

24:05.644 --> 24:07.379 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, Trump's vision is very
different.

24:07.413 --> 24:13.018 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He sees an all-of-the-above
energy strategy,
with a very heavy focus on
fossil fuels.

24:13.052 --> 24:20.526 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He sees that as really a way to
create this
American renaissance in
manufacturing and

24:20.559 --> 24:25.164 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in, you know, those good old
blue-collar jobs
that he was really talking about
very much

24:25.197 --> 24:26.565 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
on the campaign trail.

24:26.598 --> 24:29.535 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, for him, it's part of his
economic vision.

24:29.568 --> 24:34.473 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The environmental gains of the
Obama administration
were seen as an impediment to
those goals.

24:34.506 --> 24:39.511 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: All right,
Valerie Volcovici
of Reuters, thank you very much.

24:39.545 --> 24:46.785 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
VALERIE VOLCOVICI: Thank you.

